40|$|Beamline 7. 3. 3 at the <b>Advanced</b> <b>Light</b> <b>Source</b> {{combines}} a femtosecond laser system with an x-ray streak camera. Time-resolved x-ray diffraction with picosecond time resolution {{is used to}} observe scattering from coherent acoustic phonons in laser-excited InSb crystals. Synchrotron radiation pulses of ∼ 300 fs in duration have been generated by femtosecond laser pulses modulating the electron beam in the <b>Advanced</b> <b>Light</b> <b>Source.</b> © 2000 American Institute of Physics...|$|R
